15-year-old Tran left her village to look for a job in the city.

Instead of working in a restaurant as promised by a job broker, Tran was taken to a karaoke bar. Realising she was in danger, Tran ran away.

A former Blue Dragon kid saw Tran alone on the street and contacted us for help. Some food and a safe place to rest helped her recover before she received some advice on what to do next.

Now Tran is happy to be home with her mother. Next month, she will return to school and Blue Dragon will pay all the costs so she doesn’t have to worry about money.

You, too, can help Tran and other teens like her. Sign up for the Marathon Walk 2022, a global event organised in collaboration with our long-term partner @theintrepidfoundation . Every dollar you raise will give young people the chance of an education and training, keeping them safe from exploitation.

Chung and May are getting ready to walk!

Chung is one of the original founders of Blue Dragon in Vietnam, although these days he lives in Colorado where he runs a company and is raising his family. He's also the voluntary President of Blue Dragon USA.

Despite being far from Vietnam, Blue Dragon is always a cause close to his heart.
That's why he and his 9-year-old daughter May have signed up for the 2022 Marathon Walk!

On October 9, Chung and May will walk 21 km along the scenic High Line Canal Trail. For Chung and his family, this is a great way to help young people in Vietnam. By taking on the personal challenge of walking a half marathon, they will be raising money that keeps children and youth in school and training, where they are safe from human trafficking.

The Marathon Walk is organised in collaboration with our great friends at @theintrepidfoundation, and EVERY DOLLAR you raise goes to helping the kids.

Join Chung in this great event by signing up today!



And if you would like to encourage Chung and May, sponsor them here:



#BlueDragonMarathonWalk #Marathon #Walk #IntrepidFoundation #MakeADifference #HelpChildren

Emotionally overwhelmed, Hoa struggled to walk up the entrance to her house. 
Six years ago, Hoa left home for a high-paying job introduced by a friend. However, it turned out to be a trick. She was sold to a man in China as a bride and was held in captivity, unable to escape. 
This month, Blue Dragon rescued Hoa and accompanied her safely to her home in central Vietnam. Hoa is one of nine trafficking victims we’ve helped in just the past two weeks.
After years of separation, Hoa and her family are now together again. 
Human trafficking tears families apart and leaves its victims with life-long scars. 
But you can help Hoa and other victims on their way to a brighter future. 
Join the Blue Dragon Marathon Walk 2022, organised by our amazing friends The Intrepid Foundation. Your walk of 42 kilometres (or 21 kilometres for a half-marathon!) will make a difference in the lives of children, women and men who have been trafficked into slavery. 
Wherever you are in the world, lace up your shoes and change lives on October 9!
Sign up here: bdmarathonwalk2022.raisely.com

Title:
A rapid intervention saved two high school girls who were about to be trafficked into China.

The girls come from remote Dien Bien province, which shares a long, mountainous border with China. The traffickers planned to smuggle the two teenagers into China 1,000 kilometres away from their hometown, and managed to get the girls on a bus headed towards a distant border crossing.

When Blue Dragon learned about this, a frantic chain of events began. In collaboration with the local authorities, we were able to intercept the bus, follow it and stop it, right before the border crossing.

Blue Dragon is now providing emergency assistance for the two girls and will ensure they have everything they need to recover, reunite with their families and stay safe.

The crisis created by the coronavirus pandemic has made girls and women in poor rural areas more vulnerable to human trafficking. The tougher the financial struggles, the more likely potential victims are to follow traffickers under false promises of high-paying jobs and better lives.
